22-year-old Akanmu Rasheed was on Thursday sentenced to 3 months imprisonment for breaking into house by an Osun State Magistrate’s court. The police prosecutor, ASP. Fagboyinbo Abiodun, told the court that the convict committed the crime on January 5, 2020, at about 3:00am at zone 9, Oke Arungbo Osogbo. Fagboyinbo told the court that the convict did break through the fence and enter the house of one Akinsipe Emmanuel. According to the charge sheet, the offence contravened the provision of section 509 and cap 34 vol. ll law of Osun state, 2002 The convict pleaded guilty to the two charges levelled against him by the police. The Counsel to the defender, Ibrahim A. Imran apply for the bail of his client and plead the court to temper justice with mercy adding that the convict is still young and promised not to do such crime again. The police prosecutor opposed the bill of the convict. He told the court that the convict did committed similar crime on December, 31, 2019 and was arraigned before the Magistrate court 1. Magistrate, A.O Ajanaku thereby sentenced him to three months imprisonment with the option of N10,000 fine. 